Q1)
1.using hibernate we can store java objects.
2.jdbc throws many checked exceptions
3.using hibernate we can do s/w independent queries.
4.we have to write same codes again and again if using jdbc directly.

Q2)
JPA is a specification to build ORM s/w whereas Hibernate is an implementation of JPA(It is an ORM s/w).

There are 3 layers in business application architecture--
1. Presentation layer - 
This layer is used by the users(what user sees)
2. Business logic layer - 
In this layer we implements all the business logic according to the business rules.
3. Database layer - 
In this layer we store and manipulate data.
